revision.text:
'''Charles Fredrick Wiesenthal''' was a German inventor who was awarded the patent for the first known mechanical device for sewing in 1755.  One might argue that he invented the [[sewing machine]].  He was born in Germany, but was in England at the time of invention.  For his invention of a double pointed needle with an eye at one end, he received the British Patent No. 701 (1755).<ref name="sewing">{{Cite web|url=http://indecohotels.com/sewingmachinebeginning.html |title=Sewing Machine Beginning |accessdate=2012-12-17|work=Sewing}}</ref> but after in 1830 [[Barthélemy Thimonnier]] reinvented the [[sewing machine]].

